title: Veritas NetBackup: Drive Status
agents: linux
catalog: app/backup
license: GPLv3
distribution: kuhn-ruess
description:
 This check monitors the drive status of a Veritas NetBackup device
 as reported by {vmoprcmd}.

 The agent plugin {net_backup.sh} runs {/usr/openv/volmgr/bin/vmoprcmd}
 on the NetBackup host and reports the host, drive path and status of
 each drive.

 The service goes {CRIT} if any drive of the device reports a status
 other than {SCAN-TLD}, {TLD} or {ACTIVE}. Otherwise it is {OK}.

item:
 The name of the NetBackup device.

discovery:
 One service is created for each device found in the agent output.
